An earth impling jar is the result of successfully catching an Earth impling while having an empty impling jar.

This jar can be traded in individually to Elnock Inquisitor for 3 empty impling jars.

Players can also trade Elnock two Earth impling jars along with three Gourmet impling jars and one Essence impling jar for a magic butterfly net.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening an earth impling jar gives 1,257 worth of loot, on average. This means opening earth impling jars marks an average profit of −909 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −90,932 to get a medium clue scroll from earth impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.

The following drop rates are provided by Jagex, unless otherwise specified.

Impling jar[edit | edit source]

An empty impling jar is returned when removing the loot, with a 10% chance of it breaking.[1]
